🛠️ Build Server Setup – Clean Steps
________________________________________
☁️ Step 1: Create EC2 Instance
👉 Go to AWS Console:
•	EC2 → Launch Instance 
Fill Details:
•	Name: Build-Server 
•	AMI: Amazon Linux 2023 
•	Instance Type: t2.micro / t3.micro 
•	Key Pair: Create new or use existing 
________________________________________
🌐 Network Settings:
Click Edit → Add rule:
•	Type: Custom TCP 
•	Port: 8080 
•	Source: 0.0.0.0/0 
👉 Also ensure:
•	SSH (22) open 
________________________________________
▶️ Launch Instance
________________________________________
🔐 Step 2: Connect to Server
ssh -I key.pem ec2-user@<PUBLIC-IP>
________________________________________
🔧 Step 3: Install Required Tools
________________________________________
1️⃣ Update System
sudo yum update -y
________________________________________
2️⃣ Install Git
sudo yum install git -y
git --version
________________________________________
3️⃣ Install Java 17 (Corrected)
sudo yum install java-17-amazon-corretto -y
java -version
________________________________________
4️⃣ Install Maven
sudo yum install maven -y
mvn -version
________________________________________
5️⃣ Install Docker
sudo yum install docker -y
________________________________________
▶️ Start Docker
sudo systemctl start docker
sudo systemctl enable docker
________________________________________
👤 Give Docker Permission
sudo usermod -aG docker ec2-user
⚠️ IMPORTANT:
exit
Reconnect:
ssh -i key.pem ec2-user@<PUBLIC-IP>
________________________________________
⚙️ Step 4: Configure Git (Fixed mistakes)
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "your@email.com"
git config --list
________________________________________
📥 Step 5: Clone Repository
git clone https://github.com/USERNAME/ Manual-devops-setup.git
cd Manual-devops-setup
________________________________________
📂 Verify Files
ls
👉 Expected:
•	pom.xml 
•	src 
________________________________________
⚙️ Step 6: Build Application
mvn clean package
________________________________________
💡 What it does:
•	clean → removes old build 
•	package → compiles + creates JAR 
________________________________________
✅ Expected Output:
BUILD SUCCESS
________________________________________
📦 Step 7: Verify JAR File
ls target/
👉 Must show:
WebProject-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar
________________________________________
▶️ Step 8: Run Application (Important Fix)
java -jar target/WebProject-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar --server.port=8080
________________________________________
🌐 Access:
http://<PUBLIC-IP>:8080
________________________________________
🐳 Step 9: Create Dockerfile (Correct Version)
nano Dockerfile
Paste this:
FROM eclipse-temurin:17-jdk
WORKDIR /app
COPY target/WebProject-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar app.jar
EXPOSE 8080
ENTRYPOINT ["java","-jar","app.jar","--server.port=8080"]
Save:
CTRL + X → Y → Enter
________________________________________
🏗️ Step 10: Build Docker Image
docker build -t webproject-demo .
________________________________________
🔍 Verify Image
docker images
________________________________________
▶️ Step 11: Run Container (FIXED)
❌ Old (Wrong):
-p 8080:80
✅ Correct:
docker run -d -p 8080:8080 webproject-demo
________________________________________
🌐 Step 12: Access Application
http://<PUBLIC-IP>:8080
________________________________________

🎯 Final Output
Application successfully built
JAR file created
Docker image created
Container running
App accessible on browser
